name: AGF US Market Neutral Anti-Beta CAD-Hedged ETF
longDescription: The AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti-Beta CAD-Hedged ETF seeks to provide a consistent negative beta exposure to the U.S. equity market by investing primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. In seeking to achieve its investment objective, the AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF will invest primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. The AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF will construct a dollar neutral portfolio of long and short positions of U.S. equities by investing primarily in the constituent securities of the Dow Jones U.S. Thematic Market Neutral Low Beta Index (the Index) in approximately the same weight as they appear in the Index, subject to certain rules-based adjustments.
fulldescription: The AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti-Beta CAD-Hedged ETF seeks to provide a consistent negative beta exposure to the U.S. equity market by investing primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. In seeking to achieve its investment objective, the AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF will invest primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. The AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF will construct a dollar neutral portfolio of long and short positions of U.S. equities by investing primarily in the constituent securities of the Dow Jones U.S. Thematic Market Neutral Low Beta Index (the Index) in approximately the same weight as they appear in the Index, subject to certain rules-based adjustments. The performance of the AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF will depend on the difference in the rate of returns between its long positions and short positions. For example, if the AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF's long positions outperform its short positions, the AGFiQ US Market Neutral Anti Beta CAD Hedged ETF would generate a positive return.
